Sitemanager Guide
1
Open your browser and navigate to: "https://IP_Data_Collector/". You can also use
the a4conf icon on the Data Collector desktop.
2
Click on "Data-Sender" within the main menu.
Made with Scribe - https://scribehow.com 2
3
Select "Sitemanger".
4
In the "Domain" field, enter the Gatemanager domain path.
Made with Scribe - https://scribehow.com 3
5
Enter the server address in the "Server" field.
6
Move to "Advanced".
Made with Scribe - https://scribehow.com 4
7
The Sitemanager connection is set to "Always" by default, but you can change the
setting to "Only in bidirectional mode" by selecting the checkbox to suit your
preference.
Even if the SiteManager service were always active, only the Data Sender would be
reachable. Therefore, with bidirectionality closed, you would still have maximum
protection from any cyber attack and still not be able to reach the machine
network.
Made with Scribe - https://scribehow.com 5
8
You can also set a custom name for the Gate Manager, instead of using the
default a4GATE Hostname by moving the checkbox on the left side.
9
Enter the name of the custom Gate Manager in the newly created field.
Made with Scribe - https://scribehow.com 6
10
Move to "Agents".
11
This section replicates the Agent creation part(SiteManager GUI) you can find into
Gatemanager. You can start the agent creation process by selecting a "Vendor".
Made with Scribe - https://scribehow.com 7
12
Next choose a "Type".
13
Click the "Add Agent" button to add the new Agent to the table below.
Made with Scribe - https://scribehow.com 8
14
Click on the "pencil" icon next to the new Agent to fill in the blank fields.
15
After filling in the missing parameters, click on the "Save" button:
• Name
• S/N (Serial number)
• CFG (configuration IP of the device).
Made with Scribe - https://scribehow.com 9
16
Above the table there is the "+" button, that adds a new row on the "Agent" table,
then you can enter all the parameters manually and the "Export Table Data"
button, that exports the table data to a file ("generated.csv").
17
Click the "Save" button.
Made with Scribe - https://scribehow.com 10
18
Click the "Apply" button to apply the new configurations.
19
Select "Sitemanager service status" to disable the Sitemanager service. After this
operation you will be directed to the "Data Sender" page.
Made with Scribe - https://scribehow.com 11
20
Select the "Remote assistance disabled" checkbox to enable Sitemanager service
again.
21
You can now return to the Sitemanager page.
Made with Scribe - https://scribehow.com 12
22
Select the required option from "Sitemanager service commands" to start, stop or
restart the Sitemanager service.
Be careful to stop the SiteManager service since if you are connected to a4GATE
through GateManager you will be disconnected. Look at the next point where it's
shown that you must give confirmation if you actually want to stop this service.
Made with Scribe - https://scribehow.com 13
23
Click "Stop Sitemanager".
24
Select the "Reboot Data Sender" checkbox to reboot the Data Sender. Click the
"Apply" button to start the reboot.
